You decide WHO an NPC chooses to talk to right now in a campus simulator —
or whether they simply keep to themselves this moment.

Speaker (主动方):
- id    : {{ speaker.id }}
- name  : {{ speaker.name }}
- role  : {{ speaker.role }}
- traits: {{ speaker.personality | tojson }}

Situation:
- in-game time : {{ situation.sim_time }}  (weekday={{ situation.weekday }})
- room         : {{ situation.here_uid }}  ({{ situation.here_name }})
- current activity : {{ situation.current_activity }}

Co-located people the speaker could talk to:
{% for c in candidates %}- id={{ c.id }} | name={{ c.name }} | archetype={{ c.archetype }} | minutes_since_last_talk={{ c.minutes_since_last_talk if c.minutes_since_last_talk is not none else "never" }}
{% endfor %}

Everyone listed is already a valid person to approach (recently-talked people
have been filtered out). Pick the single most natural partner for the speaker
right now:
- Prefer someone whose interests / archetype fit the current activity, or whom
  the speaker hasn't talked to in a while ("never" or large minutes).
- Match personality: outgoing speakers seek lively partners; reserved ones
  pick a familiar or quiet one.
- Normally you SHOULD pick someone (the roster is small and already cooled
  down). Only return null in the rare case the activity is strictly heads-down
  and solo (e.g. an exam) where talking would be unnatural.

Output STRICTLY this single JSON object (no markdown fences, no prose):
{
  "id"       : "<the chosen candidate id; null only if talking is unnatural>",
  "rationale": "<≤ 20 Chinese chars: why this choice>"
}
